Our Guide to the 2020 Election

The Latest

Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders clashed over the weekend in a combative display of their determination to treat the New Hampshire primary as a two-person race.

Iowa Results

Mr. Buttigieg and Mr. Sanders are separated by less than one-tenth of a percentage point in the Iowa caucus results with 99 percent in. See the latest results here.

State of the Race

The muddled Iowa caucuses set in motion a tough new series of tests for the top presidential candidates that may come to a head on Tuesday in New Hampshire.
